<h3>How to Install TwoFactor Pro</h3>

<p class="lead">TwoFactor Pro extends the free TwoFactor module with enterprise-grade security features. You must have TwoFactor installed first.</p>

<h2>1. Install TwoFactor (Free Version)</h2>
<p>TwoFactor Pro requires the free TwoFactor module to be installed first. <a href="https://pixelsolutions.biz/documentation/twofactor/how-to-install-twofactor-free-version/" target="_blank">View installation instructions for TwoFactor</a>.</p>

<h2>2. Purchase License</h2>
<p>Purchase TwoFactor Pro license from <a href="https://pixelsolutions.biz/en/plugins/twofactor/" target="_blank">Pixel Solutions</a>.</p>

<h2>3. Download TwoFactor Pro</h2>
<p>Download the TwoFactor Pro module from <a href="https://pixelsolutions.biz/account/downloads/" target="_blank">your account downloads</a>.</p>

<h2>4. Install Module</h2>
<ul>
  <li>Unpack the ZIP file you downloaded in your CMS Made Simple installation's `modules` directory</li>
  <li>Go to <strong>Site Admin &gt;&gt; Module Manager</strong></li>
  <li>Click <strong>Install</strong> next to the TwoFactorPro module</li>
</ul>

<h2>5. Activate Your License</h2>
<ul>
  <li>Go to <strong>Site Admin &gt;&gt; TwoFactor Pro Settings</strong></li>
  <li>Click the <strong>License</strong> tab</li>
  <li>Enter your license key</li>
  <li>Click <strong>Verify License</strong></li>
</ul>

<p>Your CMS Made Simple installation is now protected with enterprise-grade two-factor authentication. Configure Pro features in the <strong>Settings</strong> tab.</p>

<h2>Pro Features Overview</h2>
<ul>
  <li><strong>Multiple Passkeys:</strong> Register unlimited passkeys per user (free tier allows one)</li>
  <li><strong>Physical Security Keys:</strong> Use YubiKey, Titan Key, or other FIDO2 hardware keys as a standalone login method</li>
  <li><strong>Security Key as Primary Method:</strong> Users can select "Security Key" as their primary 2FA method, separate from Passkey</li>
  <li><strong>AAGUID Detection:</strong> Automatically identifies authenticator make/model (e.g., "YubiKey 5 NFC")</li>
  <li><strong>Key Management Dashboard:</strong> Admin overview of all registered keys across all users</li>
  <li><strong>Enforce 2FA:</strong> Require all admin users to enable 2FA</li>
  <li><strong>Rate Limiting:</strong> Brute-force protection with exponential backoff</li>
  <li><strong>Trusted Devices:</strong> Remember devices for 30 days</li>
  <li><strong>User Management:</strong> View and manage all users' 2FA status</li>
  <li><strong>Security Alerts:</strong> Email notifications for suspicious activity</li>
  <li><strong>IP Blacklisting:</strong> Block malicious IP addresses</li>
</ul>
